{North is to play 4\H. East leads the \DK.

Losers:   \S = 2    \H = 1 or 2  \D = 0    \C = 0 Total = 3 or 4

In fact if trumps split 5-0 you could have 3 losers in the suit and a disaster. So we won't worry about that possibility. Since the most likely scenario is a 3-2 split you should plan on taking the \H A K, then driving out their master trump so you can run dummy's \Cs without somebody ruffing in.

Bad news. East discards a \D on the second \H lead. Time for a change in plans? 

Actually, no. West has 2 master trumps at this point but you still have \H 9 7 5 3. So use one of your little ones to drive out West's \HJ. He will probably force you to ruff a \D, leaving you with \H 9 7. Use one of them to force out West's \HQ. You still have a trump left to stop their \Ds, and as soon as you get the lead you can now run dummy's \C suit safely.

Suppose you had not driven out both of West's high trumps.

He would have ruffed the third \C, before you could discard a \S loser from your hand. You would lose two trumps and two \Ss.}
[Play "W"]DK

